article.description: Denver blows past Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 64-48
article.headline: Denver blows past Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 64-48
article.linkText: Denver blows past Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 64-48
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Cam Griffin and Nate Engesser combined for 29 points to lead Denver to a 64-48 victory over Texas A&M-Corpus Christi on Saturday. Griffin had 16, Engesser, who made 3 of 5 from beyond the arc, had 13 and Brett Olson chipped in 11. Denver held a 31-23 lead at the break and pushed that to 43-23 with 15:56 left in the game. Brandon Pye nailed a 3-point jumper to close to 50-41 with 7:36 left, but the Islanders could get no closer. The Pioneers, who shot 40 percent from long range, made 25 of 45 field goal attempts (55.6 percent) while limiting the Islanders to 15-of-43 shooting (34.9 percent). Denver (4-3) picked up 19 points off of 14 A&M-Corpus Christi turnovers. Rashawn Thomas made 6 of 12 field goal attempts to lead the Islanders (3-4). John Jordan chipped in 12.
